hpicfOspf.name: hpicfOspf

revisions.description: 1.Added hpicfOspfReferenceCost. 2.Deprecated hpicfOspfCompliance2 3.Defined hpicfOspfReferenceGroup 4.Defined hpicfOspfMetricGroup 5.Added hpicfOspfIfFlagValue 6.Defined hpicfOspfComplaince3
Added object to 1. retrieve request list of a particular interface. 2. retrieve retransmission list of a particular interface. 3. retrieve flood list of a particular interface.
Added object to 1. indicate ospf interface statistics sent, received and error packet count. 2. clear ospf statistics 3. indicate reasons for spf run.
Added object to indicate if ospf interface is passive or active
Added objects to display the NSSA route metric types.
Added objects for configuring a default administrative distance per route type.

hpicfOspf.contactinfo: Hewlett-Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. M/S 5557 Roseville, CA 95747-5557
hpicfOspf.description: This MIB module contains HP proprietary extensions to the OSPF-MIB module.

HpicfOspfRouterIdTc.name: HpicfOspfRouterIdTc
HpicfOspfRouterIdTc.description: A 32-bit, unsigned integer uniquely identifying the router in the Autonomous System. To ensure uniqueness, this may default to the value of one of the router's IPv4 host addresses if IPv4 is configured on the router.

hpicfOspf1583CompatibilityMode.name: hpicfOspf1583CompatibilityMode
hpicfOspf1583CompatibilityMode.description: Controls the preference rules used when choosing among multiple AS-external-LSAs advertising the same destination. When set to 'true', the preference rules remain those specified in RFC 1583. When set to 'false', the preference rules are those stated in RFC 2328, which prevent routing loops when AS-external-LSAs for the same destination have been originated from different areas. Set to 'true' by default. In order to minimize the chance of routing loops, all OSPF routers in an OSPF routing domain should have this object set identically. When there are routers present that have not been updated with the functionality specified in RFC 2328, all routers should have this object set to 'true'. Otherwise, all routers should have this object set to 'false', preventing all routing loops.

hpicfOspfDefaultImportMetric.name: hpicfOspfDefaultImportMetric
hpicfOspfDefaultImportMetric.description: The default metric used for advertising external routes imported into OSPF by this router.

hpicfOspfDefaultImportMetricType.name: hpicfOspfDefaultImportMetricType
hpicfOspfDefaultImportMetricType.description: The default metric type used for advertising external routes imported into OSPF by this router.

hpicfOspfIntraAreaDistance.name: hpicfOspfIntraAreaDistance
hpicfOspfIntraAreaDistance.description: The default administrative distance to associate with intra-area routes learned by OSPF. Routes with lower distances are preferred. By default, OSPF routes have an administrative distance of 110. Note that the administrative distance settings for OSPF do not affect the choice of routes within OSPF. OSPF will still prefer intra-area routes over inter-area or AS-external routes even if hpicfOspfInterAreaDistance or hpicfOspfExternalDistance is lower than hpicfOspfIntraAreaDistance. The appropriate administrative distance value is applied to the route that OSPF selects as its best route to a destination and is used to decide whether OSPF's route is preferred over a route from some other source.

hpicfOspfInterAreaDistance.name: hpicfOspfInterAreaDistance
hpicfOspfInterAreaDistance.description: The default administrative distance to associate with inter-area routes learned by OSPF. Routes with lower distances are preferred. By default, OSPF routes have an administrative distance of 110. Note that the administrative distance settings for OSPF do not affect the choice of routes within OSPF. OSPF will still prefer intra-area routes over inter-area routes, even if hpicfOspfInterAreaDistance is lower than hpicfOspfIntraAreaDistance. It will also still prefer inter-area routes over AS-external routes even if hpicfOspfExternalDistance is lower than hpicfOspfInterAreaDistance. The appropriate administrative distance value is applied to the route that OSPF selects as its best route to a destination and is used to decide whether OSPF's route is preferred over a route from some other source.

hpicfOspfExternalDistance.name: hpicfOspfExternalDistance
hpicfOspfExternalDistance.description: The default administrative distance to associate with AS-external routes learned by OSPF. Routes with lower distances are preferred. By default, OSPF routes have an administrative distance of 110. Note that the administrative distance settings for OSPF do not affect the choice of routes within OSPF. OSPF will still prefer intra-area routes and inter-area routes over AS-external routes even if hpicfOspfExternalDistance is lower than the hpicfOspfIntraAreaDistance or hpicfOspfInterAreaDistance. The appropriate administrative distance value is applied to the route that OSPF selects as its best route to a destination and is used to decide whether OSPF's route is preferred over a route from some other source.

hpicfOspfSpfThrottleWaitInterval.name: hpicfOspfSpfThrottleWaitInterval
hpicfOspfSpfThrottleWaitInterval.description: Minimum wait time between two consecutive SPFs.

hpicfOspfSpfThrottleMaxWaitTime.name: hpicfOspfSpfThrottleMaxWaitTime
hpicfOspfSpfThrottleMaxWaitTime.description: Maximum wait time between two consecutive SPFs.

hpicfOspfSpfThrottleCurrentSpfInterval.name: hpicfOspfSpfThrottleCurrentSpfInterval
hpicfOspfSpfThrottleCurrentSpfInterval.description: Current dynamic wait interval between SPF computations

hpicfOspfReferenceCost.name: hpicfOspfReferenceCost
hpicfOspfReferenceCost.description: The reference cost is used as a global configuration for internal area cost.

hpicfOspfRedistTable.name: hpicfOspfRedistTable
hpicfOspfRedistTable.description: Table for configuring route redistribution into OSPF.

hpicfOspfRedistEntry.name: hpicfOspfRedistEntry
hpicfOspfRedistEntry.description: An entry in the table for configuring route redistribution into OSPF from a single source protocol. Entries in this table are not created dynamically. There will be a single entry for each supported source protocol.

hpicfOspfRedistSrcProto.name: hpicfOspfRedistSrcProto
hpicfOspfRedistSrcProto.description: Source protocol to redistribute routes from.

hpicfOspfRedistEnabled.name: hpicfOspfRedistEnabled
hpicfOspfRedistEnabled.description: A flag indicating whether OSPF should redistribute routes from this source protocol.

hpicfOspfRedistRestrictTable.name: hpicfOspfRedistRestrictTable
hpicfOspfRedistRestrictTable.description: A table of route prefixes for filtering out routes that OSPF should not redistribute. Any route that is contained by a range in this table (in other words, has a longer mask than that specified by hpicfOspfRedistRestrictMask and where the route destination ANDed with the hpicfOspfRedistRestrictMask is equal to hpicfOspfRedistRestrictAddr) will not be redistributed as an AS-external LSA by OSPF.

hpicfOspfRedistRestrictEntry.name: hpicfOspfRedistRestrictEntry
hpicfOspfRedistRestrictEntry.description: A single entry in the table. Any route, regardless of source protocol which is contained within the specified range will not be redistributed into OSPF. Entries in this table are created dynamically using the hpicfOspfRedistRestrictStatus object.

hpicfOspfRedistRestrictAddr.name: hpicfOspfRedistRestrictAddr
hpicfOspfRedistRestrictAddr.description: The IP address of the range of route entries to exclude from redistribution into OSPF.

hpicfOspfRedistRestrictMask.name: hpicfOspfRedistRestrictMask
hpicfOspfRedistRestrictMask.description: The mask for the range of route entries to exclude from redistribution into OSPF.

hpicfOspfCompliance.name: hpicfOspfCompliance
hpicfOspfCompliance.description: The compliance statement for HP Routing Switches that support OSPF.

hpicfOspfIfTable.name: hpicfOspfIfTable
hpicfOspfIfTable.description: Extensions to the table that contains OSPF Interface specific information.

hpicfOspfIfEntry.name: hpicfOspfIfEntry
hpicfOspfIfEntry.description: A list of extensions to the information maintained for an OSPF interface.

hpicfOspfIfPassive.name: hpicfOspfIfPassive
hpicfOspfIfPassive.description: The passive state configuration of the OSPF interface. In the passive mode no OSPF protocol messages are exchanged on this interface. true (1) - The interface is configured to work in Passive mode false (2) - The interface is configured to work in normal mode. This is the default configuration. Changing the value will cause OSPF to reset on this interface and make necessary adjustments to the link state database. All other operations are not defined and will not affect the state of the protocol.

hpicfOspfIfNbrCount.name: hpicfOspfIfNbrCount
hpicfOspfIfNbrCount.description: This object specifies the number of OSPFv3 neighbors present in this interface. This counter should be incremented when a new neighbor is added in the network in which this interface is present. It should be decremented when a neighbor is disconnected.

hpicfOspfIfBfdEnbl.name: hpicfOspfIfBfdEnbl
hpicfOspfIfBfdEnbl.description: param to enable BFD under OSPF

hpicfOspfIfStatsTable.name: hpicfOspfIfStatsTable
hpicfOspfIfStatsTable.description: Table that contains OSPF Interface traffic specific information.

hpicfOspfIfStatsEntry.name: hpicfOspfIfStatsEntry
hpicfOspfIfStatsEntry.description: A list of extensions to the information maintained for an OSPF interface.

hpicfOspfSentHelloPkt.name: hpicfOspfSentHelloPkt
hpicfOspfSentHelloPkt.description: The number of OSPF Hello packets sent on the interface. This number is incremented each time an OSPF Hello packet is sent out of an OSPF enabled interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using clear ip ospf statistics command.

Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using clear ip ospf statistics command.

hpicfOspfSentLSRPkt.name: hpicfOspfSentLSRPkt

Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using clear ip ospf statistics command.

Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using clear ip ospf statistics command.

hpicfOspfRcvdDDPkt.name: hpicfOspfRcvdDDPkt
hpicfOspfRcvdDDPkt.description: The number of Database Description packets received on the interface. This number is incremented each time a OSPF DD packet is received on OSPF enabled interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using clear ip ospf statistics command.

Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using clear ip ospf statistics command.

hpicfOspfRcvdLSUPkt.name: hpicfOspfRcvdLSUPkt
hpicfOspfRcvdLSUPkt.description: The number of Link State Update packets received on the interface. This number is incremented each time a OSPF LSU packet is received on OSPF enabled interface.

hpicfOspfRcvdLSAPkt.name: hpicfOspfRcvdLSAPkt
hpicfOspfRcvdLSAPkt.description: The number of Link State Ack packets received on the interface. This number is incremented each time a OSPF LSA packet is received on OSPF enabled interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using clear ip ospf statistics command.

hpicfOspfIfErrorTable.name: hpicfOspfIfErrorTable
hpicfOspfIfErrorTable.description: Table that contains OSPF Interface traffic specific information.

hpicfOspfIfErrorEntry.name: hpicfOspfIfErrorEntry
hpicfOspfIfErrorEntry.description: A list of extensions to the information maintained for an OSPF interface.

hpicfOspfIfErrorType.name: hpicfOspfIfErrorType
hpicfOspfIfErrorType.description: The hpicfOspfIfErrorType refers to the type of errors in the OSPF packet received on any OSPF enabled interface. Errors could be Invalid RouterID/ AreaID Checksum error, OutOfbound Error ...

hpicfOspfIfErrorCount.name: hpicfOspfIfErrorCount
hpicfOspfIfErrorCount.description: The hpicfOspfErrorCount is count of each type error packet received on an OSPF interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using clear ip ospf statistics command

hpicfOspfIfClearStatsTable.name: hpicfOspfIfClearStatsTable
hpicfOspfIfClearStatsTable.description: A list used to clear statistics information maintained for an OSPF interface.

hpicfOspfIfClearStatsEntry.name: hpicfOspfIfClearStatsEntry
hpicfOspfIfClearStatsEntry.description: A list used to clear statistics information maintained for an OSPF interface.

hpicfOspfClearCounters.name: hpicfOspfClearCounters
hpicfOspfClearCounters.description: Read of this will always be false, When this variable is set to true for a given Ipaddress interface, corresponding interface counters will be cleared.

hpicfOspfSpfTable.name: hpicfOspfSpfTable
hpicfOspfSpfTable.description: Table that contains OSPF SPF information.

hpicfOspfSpfEntry.name: hpicfOspfSpfEntry
hpicfOspfSpfEntry.description: A list of extensions to the information maintained for OSPF SPF runs.

hpicfOspfSpfInstance.name: hpicfOspfSpfInstance
hpicfOspfSpfInstance.description: The hpicfospfSpfInstance refers to the instance of SPF Shortest Path First ran for an OSPF instance.

hpicfOspfSpfReason.name: hpicfOspfSpfReason
hpicfOspfSpfReason.description: The hpicfOspfSpfReason refers to the reason for scheduling an SPF run. Reasons could be OSPF init, adding/deleting interface, linkStateUpdate received.. Only last ten SPF run's reasons will be saved.

hpicfOspfSpfTime.name: hpicfOspfSpfTime
hpicfOspfSpfTime.description: The hpicfOspfSpfTime refers to the time at which SPF run is scheduled. Reasons could be OSPF init, adding/deleting interface, linkStateUpdate received.. Only last ten SPF run's reasons will be saved.

hpicfOspfReqTable.name: hpicfOspfReqTable
hpicfOspfReqTable.description: Request List table that contains OSPF Specific interface information.

hpicfOspfReqEntry.name: hpicfOspfReqEntry
hpicfOspfReqEntry.description: A Request List entries that contain fields of link state advertisement.

hpicfOspfReqType.name: hpicfOspfReqType
hpicfOspfReqType.description: The type of the Request List's link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format.

hpicfOspfReqLsid.name: hpicfOspfReqLsid
hpicfOspfReqLsid.description: The Request List's Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a Router ID or an IP address; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

hpicfOspfReqRouterId.name: hpicfOspfReqRouterId
hpicfOspfReqRouterId.description: The 32-bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

hpicfOspfReqSequence.name: hpicfOspfReqSequence
hpicfOspfReqSequence.description: The Request List's sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It starts with the value '80000001'h, or -'7FFFFFFF'h, and increments until '7FFFFFFF'h. Thus, a typical sequence number will be very negative. It is used to detect old and duplicate Link State Advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number, the more recent the advertisement.

hpicfOspfReqAge.name: hpicfOspfReqAge
hpicfOspfReqAge.description: This Request list's field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.

hpicfOspfReqChecksum.name: hpicfOspfReqChecksum
hpicfOspfReqChecksum.description: This Request list's field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagram's; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

hpicfOspfRetransTable.name: hpicfOspfRetransTable
hpicfOspfRetransTable.description: Retransmission List table that contains Ospf Interface Specific information.

hpicfOspfRetransEntry.name: hpicfOspfRetransEntry
hpicfOspfRetransEntry.description: Retransmission list entry that is maintained for an OSPF Interface.

hpicfOspfRetransType.name: hpicfOspfRetransType
hpicfOspfRetransType.description: The Retransmission List LSA type. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format.

hpicfOspfRetransLsid.name: hpicfOspfRetransLsid
hpicfOspfRetransLsid.description: The Retransmission List Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a Router ID or an IP address; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

hpicfOspfRetransRouterId.name: hpicfOspfRetransRouterId
hpicfOspfRetransRouterId.description: The 32-bit number that uniquely identifies the originating Retransmission List router in the Autonomous System.

hpicfOspfRetransSequence.name: hpicfOspfRetransSequence

It is used to detect old and duplicate Link State Advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number, the more recent the advertisement.

hpicfOspfRetransAge.name: hpicfOspfRetransAge
hpicfOspfRetransAge.description: This Retransmission List field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.

hpicfOspfRetransChecksum.name: hpicfOspfRetransChecksum

The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagram's; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

hpicfOspfFloodTable.description: Flood list table that contains Ospf Interface Specific information

hpicfOspfFloodEntry.name: hpicfOspfFloodEntry
hpicfOspfFloodEntry.description: A Flood list information maintained for an OSPF Interface

hpicfOspfFloodType.name: hpicfOspfFloodType
hpicfOspfFloodType.description: The flood list LSA type .Each link state type has a separate advertisement format.

hpicfOspfFloodLsid.name: hpicfOspfFloodLsid
hpicfOspfFloodLsid.description: The flood list Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a Router ID or an IP address; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

hpicfOspfFloodRouterId.name: hpicfOspfFloodRouterId
hpicfOspfFloodRouterId.description: The 32-bit number that uniquely identifies the originating flood list router in the Autonomous System.

hpicfOspfFloodSequence.name: hpicfOspfFloodSequence

The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagram's; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

hpicfOspfSpfTimerElapsed.name: hpicfOspfSpfTimerElapsed
hpicfOspfSpfTimerElapsed.description: The elapsed time since the last Ospf Spf is run

hpicfOspfAreaLsdbTable.name: hpicfOspfAreaLsdbTable
hpicfOspfAreaLsdbTable.description: The OSPF Process's Area-Scope LSDB. The LSDB contains the Area-Scope Link State Advertisements from throughout the area that the device is attached to.

hpicfOspfAreaLsdbEntry.name: hpicfOspfAreaLsdbEntry
hpicfOspfAreaLsdbEntry.description: A single Area-Scope Link State Advertisement.

hpicfOspfAreaLsdbRtrCapBits.name: hpicfOspfAreaLsdbRtrCapBits
hpicfOspfAreaLsdbRtrCapBits.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix A.4.2 Router LSAs
hpicfOspfAreaLsdbRtrCapBits.description: This field is valid if the LSA is a Router LSA. It uniquely identifies the router type of the router in the Area.

hpicfOspfAreaLsdbOptions.name: hpicfOspfAreaLsdbOptions
hpicfOspfAreaLsdbOptions.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix A.2 The Options field
hpicfOspfAreaLsdbOptions.description: The Options field enables OSPF routers to support (or not support) optional capabilities, and to communicate their capability level to other OSPF routers. This field is valid for each type of LSA.

hpicfOspfAreaLsdbMetric.name: hpicfOspfAreaLsdbMetric
hpicfOspfAreaLsdbMetric.description: This field is valid if the LSA is a Router LSA, a Summary LSA, AS Summary LSA or a NSSA LSA. This field indicates the cost involved in using the interface or route.

hpicfOspfAreaLsdbFwdingAddress.name: hpicfOspfAreaLsdbFwdingAddress
hpicfOspfAreaLsdbFwdingAddress.description: This field is valid if the LSA is a NSSA LSA. This field is present only if the 'F' Bit is set in the EFT flags field and if included, the data traffic for the advertised destination will be forwarded to this address.

hpicfOspfAreaLsdbExtRouteTags.name: hpicfOspfAreaLsdbExtRouteTags
hpicfOspfAreaLsdbExtRouteTags.description: This field is valid if the LSA is a NSSA LSA. This field is present only if the 'T' Bit is set in the EFT flags field. A 32-bit field which may be used to communicate additional information between AS boundary routers.

hpicfOspfTOS.name: hpicfOspfTOS
hpicfOspfTOS.description: The 32-bit identifier for the TOS specific information of the LSA.

hpicfOspfLsdbRouterLinks.name: hpicfOspfLsdbRouterLinks
hpicfOspfLsdbRouterLinks.description: This field is valid if the LSA is Router LSA. It holds the information of Number of links in the router LSA.

hpicfOspfLsdbBitE.name: hpicfOspfLsdbBitE
hpicfOspfLsdbBitE.description: The 32-bit identifier for the Metric specific information of the LSA.

hpicfOspfRouterLSATable.name: hpicfOspfRouterLSATable
hpicfOspfRouterLSATable.description: This table having Area scope is a dependent-expansion table for the Router LSA entry in the Area LSDB table. It represents the list of per interface details advertised in a Router LSA.

hpicfOspfRouterLSAEntry.name: hpicfOspfRouterLSAEntry
hpicfOspfRouterLSAEntry.description: A single Area-Scope Link State Advertisement.

hpicfOspfRouterLSANbrRtrId.name: hpicfOspfRouterLSANbrRtrId
hpicfOspfRouterLSANbrRtrId.description: The router id of the router which is connected over the interface Id.

hpicfOspfRouterLSAIfType.name: hpicfOspfRouterLSAIfType
hpicfOspfRouterLSAIfType.description: The 32-bit identifier of the Area from which the LSA was received.

hpicfOspfRouterLSAMetric.name: hpicfOspfRouterLSAMetric
hpicfOspfRouterLSAMetric.description: This field indicates the cost involved in using the interface or route.

hpicfOspfRouterLSAIfId.name: hpicfOspfRouterLSAIfId
hpicfOspfRouterLSAIfId.description: The interface Id of the router that connects to the other router.

hpicfOspfRouterLSATOSMetric.name: hpicfOspfRouterLSATOSMetric
hpicfOspfRouterLSATOSMetric.description: This field indicates the cost involved in using the interface or route specific to TOS.

hpicfOspfNetworkLSATable.name: hpicfOspfNetworkLSATable
hpicfOspfNetworkLSATable.description: This table having Area scope is a dependent-expansion table for the Network LSA entry in the Area LSDB table. This table represents the list of routers advertised in a Network LSA.

hpicfOspfNetworkLSAEntry.name: hpicfOspfNetworkLSAEntry
hpicfOspfNetworkLSAEntry.description: A single Area-Scope Link State Advertisement.

hpicfOspfNetworkLSASeqNum.name: hpicfOspfNetworkLSASeqNum
hpicfOspfNetworkLSASeqNum.description: The 32-bit sequence number identifying the attached router-ids.

hpicfOspfNetworkLSAAttachedRouter.name: hpicfOspfNetworkLSAAttachedRouter
hpicfOspfNetworkLSAAttachedRouter.description: The 32-bit Router identifier of the attached Router.

hpicfOspfExtLsdbTable.name: hpicfOspfExtLsdbTable
hpicfOspfExtLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Process's AS-Scope Link State Database (LSDB). The LSDB contains the AS-Scope Link State Advertisements from throughout the areas that the device is attached to.

hpicfOspfExtLsdbEntry.name: hpicfOspfExtLsdbEntry
hpicfOspfExtLsdbEntry.description: A single AS-Scope Link State Advertisement.
